{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/83412.A_Judgement_in_Stone", "title": "A Judgement in Stone", "titleComplete": "A Judgement in Stone", "description": "What on earth could have provoked a modern day St. Valentine's Day massacre?On Valentine's Day, four members of the Coverdale family--George, Jacqueline, Melinda and Giles--were murdered in the space of 15 minutes. Their housekeeper, Eunice Parchman, shot them, one by one, in the blue light of a televised performance of Don Giovanni. When Detective Chief Superintendent William Vetch arrests Miss Parchman two weeks later, he discovers a second tragedy: the key to the Valentine's Day massacre hidden within a private humiliation Eunice Parchman has guarded all her life.\u00a0\u00a0A brilliant rendering of character, motive, and the heady discovery of truth, A Judgement in Stone is among Ruth Rendell's finest psychological thrillers.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320497701i/83412.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Suspense", "Contemporary", "Mystery Thriller", "Crime", "Fiction", "Thriller", "British Literature", "Novels", "Detective"], "asin": "0375704965", "isbn": "0375704965", "isbn13": "9780375704963", "publisher": "Vintage Crime/Black Lizard", "author": ["Ruth Rendell"], "publishDate": 946713600000, "characters": ["Joan Smith", "Eunice Parchman", "George Coverdale", "Giles Mont", "Jacqueline Coverdale", "Norman Smith", "Melinda Coverdale"], "places": ["England"], "ratingHistogram": [127, 428, 1721, 2832, 2198], "ratingsCount": 7306, "reviewsCount": 619, "numPages": 188, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "CWA Silver Dagger", "awardedAt": 220953600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
