{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30808751-bertie-and-the-tin-man", "title": "Bertie and the Tin Man", "titleComplete": "Bertie and the Tin Man", "description": "It is 1886 and the greatest of all jockeys, Fred Archer, has put his gun to his head and shot himself. An inquest is arranged with indecent haste. His mind was unhinged by typhoid, say the jury, despite conflicting evidence.The Prince is suspicious. He admired Archer. He knows the Turf better than anyone on that jury and he has personal experience of typhoid. When he learns that Archer\u2019s last words were, \u2018Are they coming?\u2019 he decides on action. He will turn his unique talents to solving the mystery and tell us in his inimitable fashion how he does it.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1468576279i/30808751.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Historical Mystery", "Victorian", "Crime", "Fiction", "Historical", "British Literature", "Cozy Mystery", "20th Century", "Historical Fiction"], "asin": "1531875920", "isbn": "1531875920", "isbn13": "9781531875923", "publisher": "Audible Studios on Brilliance Audio", "series": ["Albert Edward, Prince of Wales"], "author": ["Terrence Hardiman", "Peter Lovesey"], "publishDate": 1474354800000, "characters": ["Albert Edward, Prince of Wales"], "ratingHistogram": [8, 45, 164, 150, 61], "ratingsCount": 428, "reviewsCount": 55, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/83429.Demon_in_My_View", "title": "Demon in My View", "titleComplete": "Demon in My View", "description": "She waits for him in the dark, her mind and body perfect, passive, until one day, when he goes to the cellar, and she is gone . . .In A Demon in My View, Ruth Rendell creates a character as frightening as he is fascinating. Mild-mannered Arthur Johnson has never known how to talk to women. And his loneliness has perverted his desire for love and respect into a carefully controlled penchant for violence. One floor below him, a scholar finishing his thesis on psychopathic personalities is about to stumble\u2014quite literally\u2014upon one of Arthur's many secrets. Haunting and intelligent, A Demon in My View shows the startling results of this chilling alchemy of two very disparate minds\u2014one pathological and the other obsessed with pathology.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1318159154i/83429.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Suspense", "Psychological Thriller", "Mystery Thriller", "Crime", "Fiction", "Thriller", "British Literature", "Detective", "Audiobook"], "isbn": "0754086445", "isbn13": "9780754086444", "publisher": "Black Dagger Crime", "author": ["Ruth Rendell"], "publishDate": 1051772400000, "ratingHistogram": [36, 133, 616, 870, 576], "ratingsCount": 2231, "reviewsCount": 171, "numPages": 214, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "CWA Gold Dagger", "awardedAt": 189331200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}]}
