{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/540020.The_Day_of_the_Jackal", "title": "The Day of the Jackal", "titleComplete": "The Day of the Jackal", "description": "Librarian note: an alternate cover for this edition can be found here.The Jackal. A tall, blond Englishman with opaque, gray eyes. A killer at the top of his profession. A man unknown to any secret service in the\u00a0 world. An assassin with a contract to kill the world's most heavily guarded man.One\u00a0 man with a rifle who can change the course of history. One man whose mission is so secretive not\u00a0even his employers know his name. And as the\u00a0minutes count down to the final act of execution, it\u00a0seems that there is no power on earth that can stop\u00a0the Jackal.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1405364996i/540020.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Crime", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Espionage", "Historical Fiction", "Novels", "Classics"], "asin": "0553266306", "publisher": "Bantam", "author": ["Frederick Forsyth"], "publishDate": 305017200000, "characters": ["Charles de Gaulle", "Claude Lebel", "Roger Frey", "Victor Kowalski", "Jacqueline Dumas", "the Jackal"], "places": ["France", "Paris"], "ratingHistogram": [1197, 2809, 17693, 49347, 62877], "ratingsCount": 133923, "reviewsCount": 2687, "numPages": 358, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Martin Beck Award", "awardedAt": 63100800000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Edgar Award", "awardedAt": 63100800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18397444-the-key-to-rebecca", "title": "The Key to Rebecca", "titleComplete": "The Key to Rebecca", "description": "\"Achmed walked alone out of the desert. He had come from the sea, from El Agela in Libya. His journey had started in Berlin on a balcony overlooking the Landwher Canal with the single comment: \"Rommel wants me to put an agent into Cairo.\" Now, Achmed opens the cases he carries with him. In one, a compact radio, in the other a book. Its first line, in English, reads: \"Last night I dreamt I went to Manderley again.\" He closes the book and removes some clothes. He shaves. He washes. Later, dressed in a brown checked suit. Achmed emerges from the tent of his cousin. He takes a wallet from the pocket of his jacket to check his papers. Alexander Wolff, age thirty-four, residing at Villa les Oliviers, Garden City. Cairo. Achmed is dead. Rommel's agent is in place. \"Cairo, 1942. Rommel and his armies are in striking distance of the city and of victory in the Mediterranean. All he needs is the key to the defenses and \"The Sphinx.\" his agent in place, is there to get it for him. Now, one renegade Englishman and one brave girl are all that can keep him out.Publisher's Summary", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1377809452i/18397444.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Suspense", "War", "Mystery Thriller", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Historical", "Espionage", "Historical Fiction", "World War II"], "publisher": "Recorded Books, Inc.", "author": ["Ken Follett", "Peter Fernandez"], "publishDate": 599644800000, "characters": ["Erwin Rommel", "Elene Fontana", "Alexander Wolff", "Anwar el-Sadat", "Joan Arbuthnot", "Colonel Reggie Bogge", "Sonja (The Key to Rebecca)", "William Vandam", "Kemel", "Major Sandy Smith", "Billy Vandam"], "places": ["Cairo"], "ratingHistogram": [352, 1518, 8851, 16411, 11106], "ratingsCount": 38238, "reviewsCount": 1440, "language": "Englis