{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11415158-the-moonstone", "title": "The Moonstone", "titleComplete": "The Moonstone", "description": "Called \"the first and greatest of English detective novels\" by T. S. Eliot, Wilkie Collins's The Moonstone is a masterpiece of suspense.  A fabulous yellow diamond becomes the dangerous inheritance of Rachel Verinder. Outside her Yorkshire country house watch the Hindu priests who have waited for many years to reclaim their ancient talisman, looted from the holy city of Somnauth. When the Moonstone disappears, the case looks simple, but in mid-Victorian England no one is what they seem, and nothing can be taken for granted. Witnesses, suspects, and detectives each narrate the story in turn. The bemused butler, the love-stricken housemaid, the enigmatic detective Sergeant Cuff, the drug-addicted scientist\u2014each speculate on the mystery as Collins weaves their narratives together.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328770162i/11415158.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Mystery Thriller", "Victorian", "Crime", "Fiction", "Literature", "British Literature", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "19th Century"], "asin": "1400169445", "isbn": "1400169445", "isbn13": "9781400169443", "publisher": "Tantor Media", "author": ["Wilkie Collins", "James Langton"], "publishDate": 1288681200000, "characters": ["Matthew Bruff", "Penelope Betteredge", "Ezra Jennings", "Rosanna Spearman", "Rachel Verinder", "Lady Julia Verinder", "Franklin Blake", "Sergeant Cuff", "Mr. Murthwaite", "Dr. Candy", "Gabriel Betteredge", "Drusilla Clack", "Godfrey Ablewhite"], "places": ["London, England", "United Kingdom", "Yorkshire, England", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [2155, 5246, 20761, 35366, 29195], "ratingsCount": 92723, "reviewsCount": 5969, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premio Euskadi de Literatura", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "Traduccion", "hasWon": null}, {"