{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10073506-tinker-tailor-soldier-spy", "title": "Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy", "titleComplete": "Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy (George Smiley, #5; Karla Trilogy, #1)", "description": "A modern classic in which John le Carr\u00e9 expertly creates a total vision of a secret world, Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy begins George Smiley's chess match of wills and wits with Karla, his Soviet counterpart. It is now beyond a doubt that a mole, implanted decades ago by Moscow Centre, has burrowed his way into the highest echelons of British Intelligence. His treachery has already blown some of its most vital operations and its best networks. It is clear that the double agent is one of its own kind. But which one? George Smiley is assigned to identify him. And once identified, the traitor must be destroyed.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1349070201i/10073506.jpg", "genres": ["Mystery", "Suspense", "Spy Thriller", "Mystery Thriller", "Crime", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Espionage", "Novels", "Classics"], "asin": "0143119788", "isbn": "0143119788", "isbn13": "9780143119784", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "series": ["The Karla Trilogy", "George Smiley"], "author": ["John le Carr\u00e9"], "publishDate": 1307430000000, "characters": ["Connie Sachs", "Bill Haydon", "Oliver Lacon", "Jim Prideaux", "Peter Guillam", "George Smiley", "Bill Roach", "Inspector Mendel", "Ann Smiley", "Toby Esterhase", "Percy Alleline", "Roddy Martindale", "Roy Bland", "Aleksey Polyakov", "Ricki Tarr"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [2127, 4775, 15820, 34138, 37071], "ratingsCount": 93931, "reviewsCount": 5402, "numPages": 381, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "CWA Silver Dagger", "awardedAt": 126259200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
